CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 8, 1957, pg. A8 reads: "Essay Contest Winners - In an essay contest, sponsored by the Allegheny County League of Women Voters, the essays of these Westinghouse students won cash awards. The subject was "How Free Enterprise Has Helped to Make America Great."  They are, left to right, seated: Bernice Parr, second place; Frank Lalento, third place, and Virginia Sprague, fifth place.  Standing: Charlene Lewis, Helen Stroud, Fred DeRubertis, Louise Nelson, Patricia Prattis and Grace Pascale, all of whom won honorable mention. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Westinghouse High School students, seated, left to right: Bernice Parr, Frank Lalento, and Virginia Sprague; standing: Charlene Lewis, Helen Stroud, Fred DeRubertis, Louise Nelson, Patricia Prattis, and Grace Pascale, posed in front of brick wainscot wall, another version
